@startuml SCRUM-9 Account Deletion

title Self-Service Account Deletion (SCRUM-9)

actor User as U
participant "Browser\n(Bootstrap modal)" as B
participant "AuthFilter" as AF
participant "DeleteAccountServlet\nPOST /protected/account/delete" as DS
participant "UserDAO" as DAO
database "PostgreSQL\n(users)" as DB
participant "SecurityUtil\n(hashPassword)" as SU
participant "HttpSession" as S

U -> B : Click Delete my account\n(open modal)
U -> B : Confirm Yes, delete my account
B -> AF : POST confirm=DELETE\n(JSESSIONID)
activate AF
AF -> DS : chain
deactivate AF

activate DS
DS -> S : getSession(false) / read userId
activate S
S --> DS : userId
deactivate S

DS -> DAO : deleteAccount(userId)
activate DAO
DAO -> SU : hashPassword(randomSecret)\n(irrecoverable placeholder)
SU --> DAO : new hash
DAO -> DB : UPDATE users SET\nemail, username, password → anonymised\nphone_encrypted, address_encrypted, 2FA → cleared\nstatus_id = DELETED\nWHERE id = ?
activate DB
DB --> DAO : 1 row
deactivate DB
DAO --> DS : true
deactivate DAO

DS -> S : invalidate()
activate S
note right of S : Session ends immediately (SCRUM-191)
S --> DS
deactivate S

DS -> B : Redirect /login?accountClosed=1\n+ no-cache headers
deactivate DS
B -> U : Login page

note over DAO, DB
  **PDPA (SCRUM-137):** row retained for auction/bid FKs;\nPII replaced with non-identifying placeholders.\nNo live email, phone, address, or usable password remains.
end note

@enduml
